          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Small business website traffic comes from multiple sources. Google Business Profile (formerly Google My Business) is critical for local businesses - it's free, puts you on Google Maps, and drives local search traffic. Local SEO optimization with city keywords and service terms helps nearby customers find you. Social media marketing on Facebook and Instagram drives followers to your website. Email signature and business cards include your website URL. Online directories like Yelp, Yellow Pages, and industry-specific listings provide backlinks and visibility. Google Ads can drive immediate traffic for urgent needs but costs money. For local businesses: Google Business Profile + local SEO + social media + email marketing = comprehensive traffic strategy. Track what works using analytics and double down on successful channels."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should small businesses use DIY builders or hire professionals?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For most small businesses, DIY AI builders are the smart choice. Cost comparison: Mixo at $9/month vs professional development at $3,000-10,000. DIY builders launch in days vs months for custom development. AI builders enable you to make updates instantly without waiting on developers or paying hourly fees. Consider hiring professionals only if: you have complex technical needs beyond AI builder capabilities, you have substantial budget ($5,000+ for website), your time is worth more than the DIY learning curve, or you need highly specialized features. For restaurants, retail, professional services, and local businesses: AI builders are completely sufficient. The $3,000-10,000 you'd spend on custom development creates far more business value when invested in marketing, inventory, equipment, or business development. Build with DIY first, upgrade only when ROI is clear."
